  "response_text": "To compare photosynthesis and cellular respiration, I'll organize the information into the following categories:\n\n1.  **Definition and Purpose**: This section will cover the basic definitions and purposes of both processes.\n2.  **Inputs and Outputs**: This section will describe the reactants and products of each process.\n3.  **Energy Transformation**: This section will explain how energy is transformed in each process.\n4.  **Location and Organisms**: This section will discuss where photosynthesis and cellular respiration occur and which organisms are involved.\n5.  **Importance and Significance**: This section will highlight the importance of each process in the ecosystem.\n\n**1. Definition and Purpose**\n\n- **Photosynthesis**: Photosynthesis is the process by which plants, algae, and some bacteria convert light energy from the sun into chemical energy in the form of glucose (C6H12O6). This process is essential for life on Earth as it provides the primary source of energy for nearly all living organisms.\n\n",
